description.p:
a) universal joint (to) composed by a spherical body (b) and an articulation cavity (5) that contains it;


b) an assembly support (c) that, inwardly, conforms to this articulation cavity (5) communicating with the exterior through an inlet mouth (4);


c) in this spherical body (b) an entrance (6) of this cable (d) whose conductors (7)(8) are connected to two respective mobile contacts slidingly (12)(14) fixed to this spherical body (b);


d) inside this cavity (5) of this assembly support (c), two fixed contacts sliding (11)(13) on those that permanently mobile support this contacts mobile (12)(14); and


e) the collisions or stop of articulation are controlled by this entrance (6) and the borders (4') of this inlet mouth (4).
